    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The farmers of western and CEN\ntrail Washington are clamoring for\nfarm laborers. The great demand\nfor this kind of help in eastern\nWashington is not as acute at pres\nent as it will be later on.\n\n\nA constant demand is made on\nemployment agencies on the Sound\nfor help at the highest wages ever\npaid. Four and five dollars per day\nis offered for harvest hands.\n\n\nJust why it is that men spurn\nthe farm work is mystery to the\nemployment agencies. The board is\nfree and food very wholesome. The\nmajority of farmers work but 10\nhours per day and the hired mans\nsalary goes on regardless of the\nweather."
    }
  ]
